getline.h declares its own int getline()/getdelim() under `#if __GLIBC__ < 2`,
i.e. only when the system libc is too old to provide them. musl provides getline
and getdelim (as ssize_t, via <stdio.h>) but does NOT define __GLIBC__, so the
bare `__GLIBC__ < 2` evaluates to `0 < 2` = true and the stale int-returning
prototypes are emitted, clashing with musl's. Guard on __GLIBC__ being defined
first, which is correct on glibc (any version), musl, and mes alike.

--- coreutils-5.0/lib/getline.h
+++ coreutils-5.0/lib/getline.h
@@ -26,7 +26,7 @@
 #  endif
 # endif

-# if __GLIBC__ < 2
+# if defined __GLIBC__ && __GLIBC__ < 2
 int
 getline PARAMS ((char **_lineptr, size_t *_n, FILE *_stream));

